    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="342"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d342">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1507.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Commissioner <persName type="from">Smith</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <lb/>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 12, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>President Báez today urgently requested conference with Commission for approval
                    of peremptory orders which he was about to have his representative deliver to
                    Arias and others for the pacification of the Cibao. His plans were approved. If
                    pacification not speedily effected President Báez will himself go there and
                    expressed wish to have one of the American Commissioners accompany him. We
                    advised him to press for early settlement of affairs through his
                    representatives.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
